        "title": "feat: add NVIDIA Brev provider",
        "body": "Closes openclaw/crabbox#289\n\n## Summary\n- add the `nvidia-brev` provider as a Linux SSH-lease backend using local Brev CLI auth\n- implement config/env/flag plumbing, provider registration, lifecycle operations, SSH config resolution, local claim handling, release, cleanup, and doctor/list behavior\n- add provider docs plus a standalone opt-in live smoke harness gated by `CRABBOX_NVIDIA_BREV_LIVE=1`\n\n## Verification\n- `go test ./internal/providers/nvidiabrev ./internal/providers/all ./internal/cli ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `go test -race ./internal/providers/nvidiabrev ./internal/providers/all ./internal/cli`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `node scripts/check-docs-links.mjs`\n- `node scripts/check-command-docs.mjs`\n- `node --test scripts/live-nvidia-brev-smoke.test.js`\n- `scripts/live-nvidia-brev-smoke.sh` -> `classification=environment_blocked reason=CRABBOX_NVIDIA_BREV_LIVE_not_enabled`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `rg -n \"nvidia-brev-(token|api-key|password|private-key)|NVIDIA_BREV_(TOKEN|API_KEY|PASSWORD|PRIVATE_KEY)\" internal docs scripts` matched only intentional negative tests / secret-surface assertions\n- `$HOME/.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main --engine codex --model gpt-5.5 --thinking medium` -> clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Notes\nThe live Brev smoke is intentionally not run by default because it can create billable GPU resources. It requires explicit local opt-in and uses local Brev CLI credentials rather than accepting Crabbox-managed secret flags.\n",
